U.K. Broadband Providers Agree on Traffic Management Code, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-14T02:46:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/u-k-broadband-providers-agree-on-traffic-management-code-ft-reports.html
Broadband service companies in the
U.K. have agreed to give customers comparable information
regarding traffic management policies, which providers say they
operate to avoid data congestion and ensure internet access, the
Financial Times reported.  A new best practice code, developed by the Broadband
Stakeholder Group, an advisory body, has been signed up to by  BT
Group Plc (BT/A) ,  Virgin Media Inc. (VMED) ,  TalkTalk Telecom Group Plc (TALK) ,  British Sky Broadcasting Group Plc (BSY) ,  Vodafone Group Plc (VOD) ,  Telefonica SA (TEF) ’s O2 unit and  Hutchison Whampoa Ltd. (13) ’s 3 U.K.
unit, the FT said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Livesey at 
 blivesey@bloomberg.net  